Each technique creates a reliable contrast layer. The scrim approach is most versatile and natural-looking.

## The Most Useful Pattern

```html
<div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-lg">
  <img src="..." />
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/20 to-transparent"></div>
  <div class="absolute bottom-4 left-4 right-4">
    <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg">Readable headline</h3>
    <p class="text-white/80 text-sm mt-1">Supporting text that's still visible</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Quick Recap

- Text over images is a readability challenge first.
- Five techniques: scrim, text box, darkening, positioning, shadow.
- Gradient scrim is most versatile.
- Always verify contrast against the darkest image version.
